programme.desc: This programme looks at the Cretaceous period, 106 million years ago. Volcanic activity forces the continents apart, and dinosaurs diversify into a range of species to cope with environmental extremes.

programme.title: Walking with Dinosaurs

programme.title: Wildest India: Western Ghats: Monsoon Mountains

programme.title: Wildest India: Thar Desert: Sacred Sands

programme.title: Wildest India: Ganges: River of Life

programme.sub-title: Venezuela: The Treasure of El Dorado

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: Pantanal: Brazil's Wild Heart

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: The Andes: World in the Clouds

programme.sub-title: The Andes: World in the Clouds

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: Amazon: One Jungle, Many Worlds

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: Patagonia: The Ends of the Earth

programme.sub-title: Patagonia: The Ends of the Earth

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Virungas: Land of Ice and Fire

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: MANMADE
programme.desc: When it comes to disasters, mother nature has mankind beat. However, as mankind expands, evolves and technology advances, it comes with dangerous challenges. When errors are made or unforeseen circumstances occur, the results can be devastating.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: TORNADO
programme.desc: A tornado is a violently rotating column of air extending from the base of a thunderstorm down to the ground. Tornadoes are capable of completely destroying well-made structures, uprooting trees, and hurling objects through the air like deadly missiles.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: MEGAFLOODS
programme.desc: Water covers two thirds of the earth’s surface, and we are utterly dependent on it, but when this vital ingredient of life unleashes its fury on the planet it becomes the ultimate bringer of death.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: EARTHQUAKES
programme.desc: Earthquakes happen when tectonic plates suddenly slip causing shock waves to shake the surface of the Earth. They occur on fault lines - the most active are the Ring of Fire in the Pacific Ocean and the San Andreas fault on America’s west coast.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: CONSTRUCTION
programme.desc: Bridges and tunnels have transformed the way we live, making the inaccessible easy to reach, and turning time consuming journeys into convenient commutes, but when things go wrong they can go very wrong indeed.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: AIR, LAND AND SEA
programme.desc: Planes, trains and ships, our mass transit systems, have had a profound effect on mankind, making the world smaller and more connected.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: HURRICANES
programme.desc: Hurricanes, Typhoons and Cyclones all the same thing with different names – what they also have in common is their destructive power! Hurricanes are large, swirling storms and winds from a hurricane can damage buildings or trees.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: VOLCANOES
programme.desc: Volcanoes are Earth’s geologic architects. They’ve created more than 80 percent of our planet’s surface and their explosive force has crafted both mountains and craters.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Wild Weather Season
programme.desc: 2005 seemed to be the year that Earth went wild. Follow George as he brings us back to the site of his hairiest adventures from that year.

programme.title: Angry Planet: West Coast Winter Weather
programme.desc: On Canada's rugged West Coast, George ice-climbs a frozen waterfall, uses ski-skins to climb Mt.Garibaldi to an alpine lake, visits a storm-watching lodge on British Columbia's Long Beach, home of winter surfing and massive Pacific storms.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Waterspouts
programme.desc: In the Florida Keys, George uses a motorboat, a van and small plane to get up close to waterspouts - the nautical cousins of tornadoes. He also meets some of the 25 million alligators that live in the Sunshine State.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Island Caving
programme.desc: Accompanied by a group of hardcore cavers from Alberta and British Columbia, George descends into spectacular caves that lead deep into the earth on Vancouver Island. The team carries inflatable kayaks to explore a dark underground river.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Desert Monsoon
programme.desc: Enlisting the help of fellow storm chaser R.J. Evans, George heads to Arizona to photograph spectacular lightning storms triggered by the desert monsoon season. R.J. however is known as "America's noisiest athiest" for his free-thought radio show.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Polynesian Volcanoes
programme.desc: In New Zealand, George learns that an undersea volcano 1000 miles North in Tonga is creating a new island. After nautical mishaps, clad in nothing but underwear and a life jacket, George becomes one of the first explorers on this new land.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Java: Land of Fire
programme.desc: In the Pacific Ring of Fire island of Java, George explores new ash eruptions from Anak Krakatau, whose 1883 eruption shook the world. He travels to Merapi and descends into Kawah Ijen to explore the world's largest lake of sulfuric acid.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Highway to Hail
programme.desc: George and his team head into "bears' cage", looking to get beat up by the biggest, baddest hailstones in Texas and Oklahoma. Their storm chasing vehicles don't look too pretty after coming through these massive storms.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Costa Rica
programme.desc: George explores the volcanoes of Costa Rica with an international team of scientists, rafts down white water rivers in full flood, rappels down raging waterfalls, and handles some of deadliest snakes this tropical country has to offer.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Winds Of Autumn
programme.desc: This year he starts off by getting prepared in a wind tunnel, then he and his chase partner Mark Robinson head to Newfoundland for more wild weather action. Then, it's off to another encounter where the wild wind fans a raging inferno.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Iceland: Fire and Ice
programme.desc: George meets President of Iceland Ólafur Grímsson who spearheaded use of geothermal power; visits Blue Lagoon and geysers; explores volcanically active Haimaey Island and climbs an iceberg calving off the glaciers at Vatnajokull Lagoon.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Hurricane Triple Threat
programme.desc: George chases deadly hurricanes in the USA: Gustav in Louisiana and Hanna in North Carolina. He then flies with USAF Hurricane Hunters into Ike over Cuba, meeting it again as it makes a wild destructive landfall in Galveston, Texas.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Timbuktu: Birthplace of Hurricanes
programme.desc: Dust storms can spin off from Africa into the Atlantic and morph into tropical hurricanes that threaten the Caribbean and USA. While searching for Timbuktu's dust storms, George finds adventure in the landscape and culture of West Africa.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Antarctica
programme.desc: From "Fin Del Mundo," George sails on a Russian icebreaker to Antarctica. After braving stormy Drake passage, he explores volcanic Deception Island, camps in Antarctic snow and paddles a kayak through icebergs calved off melting glaciers.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Eco-Disasters
programme.desc: Uzbekistan's Aral Sea, once one of the largest freshwater lakes in the world, shrunk to 1/6 its previous size; a Crimea mountain carved into a submarine base; Chernobyl nuclear site reduced to a radioactive wasteland.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Under Pressure
programme.desc: After submarine exploration of Grand Cayman Island, George dives with Canadian Armed Forces' experimental deep pressure unit. With explorers Chris Harvey-Clark and Phil Nuytten he investigates newly discovered "Black Smoker" deep sea vents.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Wild Water
programme.desc: In this episode, George investigates the wild side of water in dangerous class 5 river rapids, a flooded cave, and even in the ocean surrounded by massive Great White Sharks.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Fin Del Mundo
programme.desc: Although he admits to not being much of a sailor, George climbs aboard a sailing vessel to explore the extreme southern tip of South America (Fin Del Mundo aka the "End of the World").

programme.title: Angry Planet: Blizzards
programme.desc: Winter weather can be even more dangerous than thunderstorms and where else to explore the big chill than at the summit of Mount Washington which has the reputation as being the place with the "Worst weather in the world".

programme.title: Human Prey: Killers of the Savannah
programme.desc: Focused on helping a pregnant, wounded lioness, an unarmed South African conservationist unwittingly ends up face-to-face with one of the pride's aggressive, young males. During his Zambezi River adventure, a pilot is attacked by a hungry hyena.

programme.title: Africa River Wild
programme.desc: The Limpopo River flows along a 1000 mile course through South Africa and Mozambique and out into the Indian Ocean. Four months of the year, this powerful river continuously revitalizes the landscape nourishing the abundance of wildlife dependent on it.

programme.title: Africa River Wild
programme.desc: The Sand River is home to one of the densest and diverse animal populations in Africa, where territories dangerously intertwine and overlap. Animal mothers struggle to try and raise offspring to adulthood without them being killed.

programme.title: Africa River Wild
programme.desc: The Zambezi River rises from a marsh in Zambia. It then flows east carving a path across six different African countries before it drains out into the Indian Ocean. The river creates one world in the wet season and another in the dry season.

programme.title: Africa River Wild
programme.desc: The Hoanib River runs for around 170 miles. It rises in the Hoanib Valley in Namibia and flows through the parched Namib Desert all the way to the Skeleton Coast before emptying out into the Atlantic Ocean.

programme.title: Africa River Wild
programme.desc: In Northern Botswana lies the magnificent Okavango Delta one of the most extraordinary ecosystems in Africa. In the heart of the Kalahari Desert, it’s a wetland surrounded by parched and arid plains.

programme.title: Africa River Wild
programme.desc: On the Luangwa River, the law of the land is dictated by the changing seasons and the constant cycle of life. In the wet season, the Luangwa Valley is a green paradise. The river’s waters flow in abundance and lush vegetation carpets the landscape.

programme.title: Africa River Wild
programme.desc: The Nile River, Africa’s largest, longest and most ancient of rivers. Spanning 4000 miles the Nile flows through 11 countries before finally emptying out into the Mediterranean. For millennia its waters have sustained life and civilization.

programme.title: When Sharks Attack: Fiordland National Park
programme.desc: Sharks are the ocean’s ultimate predator. At the top of the food chain, many species of sharks are capable of killing quickly and efficiently anything they attack.

programme.title: Panda Nursery
programme.desc: Witness an amazing partnership between humans and pandas as together they raise two tiny twin cubs in an effort to increase the world’s wild panda population.

programme.title: African Bambi
programme.desc: Set in eastern Africa, "African Bambi" follows a diverse collection of gazelles on a journey of growth and survival that will test their limits, and captures the unique beauty of one of the most spectacular places on earth.

programme.title: Dark Side of Crocs
programme.desc: Nile crocodiles, one of the most impressive creatures in the world, live in groups in African rivers. Water comes and goes in the wilds of Africa and while all animals need access to water, few can call the river home.

programme.title: Hippo Supremacy
programme.desc: Zambia's Luangwa river hippos are living the easy life, or so it seems. Their life fluctuates between the serenity of sunbathing to the terrible brutality of dominance and aggression.

programme.title: Cheetahs Against All Odds

programme.title: World's Greatest: Glaciers
programme.desc: Clinging to the world’s highest mountains and forming ice caps on both poles, glaciers leave an impression on the landscape and on all who bear witness to their splendor.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Flights
programme.desc: Our experience of the world’s greatest marvels is literally and figuratively elevated when we explore them from the air. Whether you travel by air balloon, helicopter, light aircraft, a grand perspective is always guaranteed.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Coasts
programme.desc: Along coasts, one element ends and another begins. No two days are ever the same on a coastline: the only thing that remains a constant is the timeless power of the sea.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Sacred Sites
programme.desc: Ancient in architecture and detailed in design, these man-made masterpieces stand as testaments to the strength of human faith. These sites endure as a timeless reminder of resilience, respect, and the need to reflect.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Rivers
programme.desc: Rivers flow freely - beautiful and powerful waterways that underscore the melody of life. As they meander through the landscape, they shape it, wearing down ranges and deepening valleys, eventually flowing out into the sea.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Monuments & Landmarks
programme.desc: Many of the world’s most significant manmade wonders serve not as dwellings, but as powerful signposts. But more than giving us direction, they tell us a story - they characterize powerful forces, or commemorate power lost.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Jungle Animals
programme.desc: Encounter gorillas and orangutans, killer tree-dwelling pythons, delightful monkeys, awe-inspiring tigers, and millions of land-dwelling red crabs in Australia, the islands of Southeast Asia, Africa, and the Amazon.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Mountains
programme.desc: The earth’s fragile crust has folded and faulted, and nowhere are these natural forces more evident than in the world’s great mountains. Explore the highest peaks of the world’s terrain - the rugged realm between heaven and earth.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Forest Animals
programme.desc: Forest Animals gets up close with bears, koalas, moose, wolves, weaver ants, and Tasmanian Devils. This episode roves dark forests floors and soars above vast canopies of green in America, China, Laos, and Australia.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Ancient Cities
programme.desc: In Ancient Cities, we journey to these ancestors of influence such as Luang Prabang, Vienna, and Istanbul where religious and cultural centers have shaped the ways in which we view the world around us and continue to do so in modern times.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Wetland Animals
programme.desc: Wetland Animals dives into the swamps, rivers, and flood plains of the Everglades, Botswana’s Okavango Delta, Kakadu National Park in Australia, and the Amazon to see deadly crocodiles, piranhas, hippopotamus, flamingo, manatee, and platypus.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Island Nations
programme.desc: Though many are small in stature, they have punched well above their weight on the global stage. Some are rooted in ancient history, while others are only just beginning to realize their full potential.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Cruises
programme.desc: There is something seductive about setting sail. Cruises offer us a chance to dip our toes into the 70% of our planet awash with oceans, rivers, and lakes, exploring places that can only be reached by daring to leave the shore.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Grassland Animals
programme.desc: Grasslands are the great stages of the natural world where large animals play out spectacular lives in clear view of people, including lions, leopards, elephants, rhinoceros, cheetahs, impalas, kangaroos, wallaby, potoroo, bison, and wolves.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Land Adventures
programme.desc: Most land adventures come with some risk - a chance to confront our deepest fears, resist the pull of the ordinary, and soar into the wild unknown.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Marine Animals
programme.desc: From the surprises of colorful reef characters to effervescent penguins, killer sharks, and regal whales, dive into the places where nature reveals itself in some of its most marvelous and bizarre forms.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Bridges
programme.desc: A bridge is a structure that’s designed to transcend, but a great bridge can define the place where it stands. Symbols of human ingenuity, beauty, and grandeur, bridges connect us not only to each other but also to the past.

programme.title: Nazi Hunters: Kurt Lischka
programme.desc: Nazi Hunters looks at how German housewife Beate Klarsfeld and her husband Serge helped track down former Paris Gestapo chief Kurt Lishka. Lishka ordered the arrest and murder of over 33,000 Jews.

programme.title: Nazi Hunters: Joseph Mengele
programme.desc: Nazi Hunters examines how Mossad agents from Israel spent nearly thirty years tracking the notorious Nazi physician Josef Mengele. After the war, Mengele flees to Argentina where he lives a relatively nondescript life.

programme.title: Nazi Hunters: Erich Priebke
programme.desc: Nazi Hunters examines how, a half-century after the war, American journalists track down former Gestapo officer Erich Priebke. Priebke who was responsible for some of Italy's worst atrocities fled to Argentina after the war.

programme.title: Nazi Hunters: Klaus Barbie
programme.desc: Nazi Hunters looks at how the husband and wife team of Serge and Beate Klarsfeld worked tirelessly to have Nazi war criminal Klaus Barbie extradited from Bolvia to stand trail in France.

programme.title: Nazi Hunters: Adolf Eichmann
programme.desc: Nazi Hunters examines the capture of Adolf Eichmann considered by many to be one of the main architects of the Holocaust. Eichmann was captured outside of his home near Buenos Aires in Argentina by Mossad agents.

programme.title: Nazi Hunters: Herbert Cukurs
programme.desc: Nazi Hunters examines how Israeli secret service agents traveled to South America to assassinate Nazi war criminal Herbert Cukurs. Known as the Hangman of Riga, Cukurs was responsible for the deaths of over 30,000 Latvian Jews.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: Hitler's Killer Police
programme.desc: In Ukraine and Lithuania, Nazi invaders were welcomed as liberators. In Lithuania, Antanas Gecas led a militia that executed hundreds of Jews. Ukrainian nationalists participated in pogroms slaughtering 34,000 Jews in two days.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The Good Collaborators?
programme.desc: Finland defended itself in the Winter War under Marshal Mannerheim. Finland allied with Nazi Germany against the Soviet Union in 1941. Finland later negotiated peace with the Allies and switched sides as Nazi defeat became apparent.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The Dutch Collaborator
programme.desc: Anton Adriaan Mussert, initially resisted Hitler’s anti-Semitism despite modeling his NSB party, even welcoming Jewish members. His failed attempt to kidnap Queen Wilhelmina led him into hiding, after which he collaborated in hopes of gaining power.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The Jews Who Fought for Hitler
programme.desc: In Hitler’s Germany, those with Jewish ancestry faced harsh Nuremberg Laws. Full Jews faced death; Mischlinge endured discrimination, job bans. Some, like Helmut Schmidt, unaware of heritage, found protectors like Milch in high places.
programme.sub-title: The Jews Who Fought for Hitler

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The Grand Mufti
programme.desc: The controversy surrounding Mohammad Amin al-Husayni, stems from his Nazi collaboration. He recruited Bosnian Muslims and advocated for a Palestinian homeland with Nazi help. His diaries reveal awareness of the Holocaust and anti-Semitic sentiments.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The IRA Conspiracy
programme.desc: During WWII, the IRA's "S Plan" aimed to bomb Britain, drawing German support to weaken the British. "Operation Green" and "Plan Kathleen" envisioned IRA aiding a German invasion of Northern Ireland, but both failed due to bungling and infighting.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The Arajs Kommando
programme.desc: Viktor Arajs, a Latvian, played a significant role in the Holocaust, collaborating with the Nazis to eliminate Jews. Leading the Arajs Kommando, he orchestrated the killings of around 30,000 Jews. Arajs justified his actions as patriotic defense.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: Vidkun Quisling
programme.desc: Vidkun Quisling, once honored for diplomacy, turned traitor by collaborating with Nazis. His bid for power in Norway failed, relegated by Germans. Despite being named "fuehrer," his reign led to repression until his hanging post-Nazi defeat.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The Devil's Due
programme.desc: During WWII, Greek Prime Ministers Tsolakoglou, Logothetopoulos, and Rallis collaborated with Nazi occupiers, imposing fees that caused a famine.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The Croatian Collaborator
programme.desc: Croatia grapples with its fascist past through figures like Dinko Sakic, once hailed as a hero but later convicted of war crimes. Leading the notorious Jasenovac camp, Sakic oversaw brutal atrocities against inmates.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The Belgian Collaborator
programme.desc: Leon Degrelle, a charismatic Belgian leader, joined the Nazis and led Die Wallonien on the Eastern Front. Despite no military background, he earned the Knight's Cross for valor. He recruited 4000 more for the SS, defending Berlin until April 1945.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: Traitor-in-Chief
programme.desc: Pierre Laval, once celebrated and later reviled, faced execution in 1945 for collaboration with the Nazis during Vichy France. Originally a socialist and pacifist, he fell into collaboration for power and to navigate the horrors of occupation.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: By Night & By Day
programme.desc: By Night & By Day: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain, and the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: Terror of The World
programme.desc: Terror of the World: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain, and the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: X-Rated
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler had a depraved sex life that he tried to keep hidden from the German public. He was said to be a chronic masturbator, a voyeur and that he engaged in sado-masochistic sex with women.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Body Image
programme.desc: Hitler wanted the world to believe he possessed super-human qualities but in private he was a wreck. This episode reveals the archives that confirm Hitler’s genital deformity, the alarming truth about his heavy drug addiction and the Parkinson’s.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Family Matters
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler's father was a violent, abusive man. His mother doted on her young son. This episode delves deep into the psychology of Hitler as the narcissistic child who grew into a malignant psychopath full of rage and deep hatred.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Suicidal Maidens
programme.desc: Using extensive archival research, this program explores the squalid secrets he lied and killed to protect

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: The Lost Continent (Atlantis)
programme.desc: As the Nazis rose to power, Himmler and the SS were convinced Atlantis could be found, and instigated a series of archeological expeditions seeking uncover and exploit its secrets.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Walking with Witches
programme.desc: Convinced the medieval witch trials were a Judeo-Christian attempt to exterminate the Aryans, Himmler established a special team led by Reinhard Heydrich to build a database of medieval German witchcraft practices.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: The Quest for the Holy Grail
programme.desc: Revealing the work of a secret team of scientists and scholars established by SS leader Heinrich Himmler to scour the globe seeking the origins of the Aryan race and collect ancient artifacts.
programme.sub-title: The Quest for the Holy Grail

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Into the Mountains (Tibet)
programme.desc: Revealing the work of a secret team of scientists and scholars established by SS leader Heinrich Himmler to scour the globe seeking the origins of the Aryan race and collect ancient artifacts.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Cro Magnon
programme.desc: The debate about humanity's true origins becomes a nefarious fixation as SS leader Heinrich Himmler turns his attention to proving the Paleolithic past of Germany's Aryan race.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Runes
programme.desc: Runes are the letters of an ancient Germanic writing system that harkens back to a mythological age filled with heroes, magic, and mystery.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: From The "Protection Squadron" To The SS State.
programme.desc: From the Protection Squadron to the SS State: Trace the rise to power of the SS as we examine several perpetrators. Who was recruited? And why was the SS attractive to men?
programme.sub-title: From The "Protection Squadron" To The SS State.

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Adolf Hitler

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Josef Goebbels

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Julius Streicher

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Hermann Goering
programme.desc: Hermann Goering: Hermann Goering was the commander-in-chief of the Luftwaffe and Hitler's designated successor. This is his dark story.

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Albert Speer
programme.desc: Albert Speer: The career of Albert Speer, Hitler's architect, is explored in this documentary of dark figures.

programme.title: Teen Mom UK: Be My Valentine
programme.desc: Amber, Chloe and Mia have very different Valentine's Day experiences, Megan has her baby shower and Sassi and Darren reach breaking point. (S2, ep3)

programme.title: Teen Mom UK: Home Sweet Home
programme.desc: It's never a quiet life for our teen mums. Sassi plasters over the cracks, Megan prepares for her big day, Amber's love life is in tatters, Chloe buys a house and the all-new Mia is here! (S2, ep4)

programme.title: Catfish UK: Esther & Theo
programme.desc: Esther's finally found her match in Theo. But he always refuses to video call. So it's up to Julia and Oobah to find out if Theo is who he says he is. (S1, ep6)

programme.title: Catfish UK: Mario & Hannah
programme.desc: After turning his life around, Mario met his soulmate, Hannah. But she refuses to speak on the phone and won't meet in person. Julie and Oobah try to find out who his dream girl really is. (S1, ep7)

programme.title: Catfish UK: Angelica & Jeroen
programme.desc: Angelica's been speaking to Jeroen online for three and a half years. After several failed attempts to meet, she's now desperate to find out if Jeroen is real? (S2, ep5)

programme.title: Catfish UK: Hayley & Alex
programme.desc: Oobah is joined by Catfish US royalty Kamie to help Hayley finally meet Alex. But after five months of avoiding phone calls and cancelling on her, will she get her a fairy tale ending? (S2, ep4)

programme.title: Catfish UK: Cole, Abbie & The Fanpage
programme.desc: Cole and Abbie keep being sent anonymous creepy gifts to their home and their relationship is now at breaking point. Julie and Oobah head to Scotland to try and help save their marriage. (S1, ep4)

programme.title: Catfish UK: Neil & Jasmin
programme.desc: Neil has been chatting to Jasmin for 3 years and she's stood him up 13 times. So it's up to Julie and Oobah to find out if the person Neil has fallen for...is real? (S1, ep2)

programme.title: Catfish UK: Emma & Harlin
programme.desc: Julie and Oobah uncover more than they were expecting, as their search to help Emma find her online love Harlin takes a sinister turn. (S1, ep1)

programme.title: Catfish UK: Jordan & Austin
programme.desc: After two years of chatting, Jordan believes Austin is the one. But every time they arrange to meet, Austin cancels. Can Julie and Oobah finally bring them together? (S1, ep9)

programme.title: 48 Hours: The Preacher's Passion
programme.desc: A preacher searches for answers about his girlfriend's death.

programme.title: 48 Hours: Walking Free
programme.desc: The story of David Camm, who was convicted in two murder trials -- each eventually overturned -- and was found not guilty in his third trial for the murder of his wife and two children.

programme.title: 48 Hours: Spies, Lies and Secrets
programme.desc: A report about the death of Shane Todd, a brilliant, high-tech engineer at a Singapore company who, according to his parents, was murdered because he was unwilling to share secrets that could harm the United States.

programme.title: 48 Hours: Fateful Connection
programme.desc: A report on the investigation led by a determined detective to solve a 30-year-old cold case involving two young women who went missing in Florida, in 1982.

programme.title: 48 Hours: The Blue River Murder
programme.desc: A report on the investigation into the 2010 death of Stephanie Roller, a Colorado mother of three who allegedly went for a walk during a blizzard and was later found dead in a nearby river.

programme.title: 48 Hours: Death at Cottonwood Creek
programme.desc: Frederick Mueller says while he and his wife were out for a walk near their vacation home, she fell off a cliff while he stopped to take a photo of her. Was it murder or an accident?

programme.title: 48 Hours: Loved to Death
programme.desc: An investigation into the rise of violence surrounding relationship breakups among adolescents, as detailed in the story of Wayland, Massachusetts teen Lauren Astley, whose last encounter with her football player ex-boyfriend proved to be fatal

programme.title: 48 Hours: Last Chance
programme.desc: Attorneys work to get a death row inmate who confessed to a crime he didn't commit out of prison.

programme.title: Let it Snow
programme.desc: Apollo Resorts buys small businesses, tears them down, and builds giant tourist traps in their place. But when Stephanie Beck shows up at Snow Valley Lodge, she gets swept up in the Christmas spirit.

programme.title: Holiday Hearts
programme.desc: While planning an annual Christmas party, Peyton is forced together with Ben to care for a friend's daughter. While finding their Christmas spirit, will there be some romance along the way?

programme.title: Ghosts of Christmas Past
programme.desc: Ellie is told by a fortune teller that she must resolve her past and make amends with all of those she ghosted before Christmas and discovers love in the process.

programme.title: A Gift Wrapped Christmas
programme.desc: A personal shopper Gwen's newest client, Charlie, is a high-rolling, workaholic, single father.

programme.title: Christmas Comes Twice
programme.desc: Cheryl is the top newscaster who has achieved her dreams but has regrets about the guy who got away five years earlier. When the Christmas carnival comes to town, a ride around the carousel takes her back in time...

programme.title: Our Italian Christmas Memories
programme.desc: The Colucci siblings, in an effort to jog the memory of their grandfather who is struggling with dementia, set out to recreate their late grandmother’s legendary pasta sauce.

programme.title: A Snow Capped Christmas
programme.desc: When champion figure skater Claire becomes injured she is sent to a rehabilitation center in the snowy mountains where she meets and falls for a local ice fisherman who shows her there is more to life than competition.

programme.title: Christmas Festival of Ice
programme.desc: When Emma finds out that her beloved ice-sculpting contest, part of her hometown's Christmas festival, has been canceled, she springs into action.

programme.title: Baby, It's Cold Inside
programme.desc: When a travel agent up for a promotion is directed to forgo her tropical vacation to instead visit the world-famous Ice Hotel, she discovers her sacrifices are more than compensated.

programme.title: A Godwink Christmas: Miracle of Love
programme.desc: Brought together by community service, Eric and Joy find new purpose at Christmas. As they help a family rebuild their home, coincidences and a medical miracle lead them to believe in destiny.

programme.desc: Dennis Basso gowns; Mo's Bows; Jet Boots; vegan, gluten-free eyeshadow.

programme.title: Junior
programme.desc: Reflecting our society, the world of junior hockey is obsessed with competition. Taking in one complete season with the Baie-Comeau Drakkar, this film reveals the daily lives of managers and players on this Quebec Major Junior Hockey League team.

programme.title: Paul Kane Goes West
programme.desc: in the mid-1800s, Paul Kane painted the northwest, Indigneous Peopless, Chiefs, ceremonies, war parties, buffalo hunts, rapids and waterfalls. In this film his paintings are projected with lighting that brings to life every glowing detail.

programme.title: The Tree That Remembers
programme.desc: In 1992, an Iranian student took his life in Ontario, haunted despite refuge in Canada. Masoud Raouf's 'The Tree that Remembers' unites former political prisoners, honoring the dead and celebrating resilience with testimony, footage, and art.

programme.title: Doctor Lawyer Indian Chief
programme.desc: A tribute to Indigenous women everywhere, this short documentary focuses on 5 women from across Canada. They talk about the importance of Indigenous culture in helping them to develop a sense of self and seeing through rough times.

programme.title: Sunrise Over Tiananmen Square
programme.desc: Shui-Bo Wang's animated documentary intertwines personal journey with history, exploring China's '60s-'80s upheavals. From symbol of hope to tragedy, it depicts Wang's roles from Red Guard to teacher, exploring idealism and intolerance.

programme.title: Unarchived
programme.desc: In community archives across British Columbia, local knowledge keepers are fighting for a more inclusive history through family photos, newspaper articles and deeply rooted memories.

programme.title: Churchills Island
programme.desc: A classic presentation of the strategy of the Battle of Britain, the film shows, with penetrating clarity, the relationship of the various forces that went to make up the island's defenses. The first NFB film to win an Oscar.

programme.title: How They Saw Us Is It A Womans World
programme.desc: This film, made especially for television in 1956, embodies the conventional myth that women indirectly exercise power through their ability to manipulate men through sex and marriage.

programme.title: Julie Obrien
programme.desc: This film is loosely structured around Julie O'Brien, eleven’s school assignment to write an essay about the old times in Newfoundland, how they have changed, how they are still remembered.

programme.title: Theodore Ushev Unseen Connections
programme.desc: Theodore Ushev, the auteur behind a number of renowned animated shorts, reveals his inner universe, formed by a half-century of personal experience acquired in a constantly changing world.

programme.title: Beautiful Lennard Island
programme.desc: Steven Holland, age ten, is the son of the lighthouse-keeper in charge of Lennard Island, a tiny place west of Vancouver Island. He takes us on a tour and dispels any ideas we might have that living in isolation is boring.

programme.title: The Street
programme.desc: A poignant adaptation of Mordecai Richler's short story candidly depicts families' responses to aging members. Through watercolor and ink, the filmmaker captures raw family emotions, reflecting harsh realities.

programme.title: A Mother And Daughter On Abortion
programme.desc: The document of an intimate conversation between a mother and her adult daughter. They speak candidly about their personal experiences in trying to obtain an abortion, and how, in different decade, each got caught up in the system and its rules.

programme.title: Strings
programme.desc: Strings: a haunting film of intimate strangers linked by shared spaces. Comfortable connections fracture when a problem arises. Created with glass painting and stop-motion, it's visually stunning.

programme.title: Ill Find A Way
programme.desc: When nine-year-old Nadia is allowed to attend a regular school, she knows the kids will tease her but she'll "find a way to deal with it." Nadia has spina bifida, a congenital condition that has caused a lack of sensation from the knees down.

programme.title: Canada Vignettes Log Drivers Waltz
programme.desc: A young girl who loves to dance and is ready to marry chooses a log driver over his more well-to-do, land-loving competition. Driving logs down the river has made him the best dancing partner to be found.

programme.title: Children Of War
programme.desc: A remarkable documentary in which teenagers from war-torn countries, filmed in interaction with Canadian high-school students, speak with dignity, maturity and candor about the struggles of their people and the suffering they have endured.

programme.title: Chile Obstinate Memory
programme.desc: A generation of young Chileans has grown up with no knowledge of the facts surrounding the military coup of September 11, 1973. Now, Patricio Guzmán returns to Chile, after 23 years. The time has come to reveal the long-forgotten truth.

programme.title: The Sweater
programme.desc: Roch Carrier narrates a childhood mishap in "The Hockey Sweater." In rural Quebec, boys idolize Maurice "Rocket" Richard. When the protagonist receives a Toronto Maple Leafs jersey instead of a Canadiens one, embarrassment ensues at the local rink.

programme.title: Unwanted Soldiers
programme.desc: Filmmaker Jari Osborne discovers her father's WWII involvement, revealing discrimination against Chinese-Canadians. His secret missions in Southeast Asia shed light on their quiet heroism, paying moving tribute in this multi-layered documentary.

programme.title: Bobs Birthday
programme.desc: Surprise birthday parties can be risky. Especially when the guest of honour is turning 40! When Margaret plans a celebration for her husband, Bob, she underestimates the sudden impact of middle age on his mood.

programme.title: The Lost Pharaoh The Search For Akhenaten
programme.desc: This documentary tells the fascinating story of an ancient pharaoh who was almost lost to history, and the archaeological sleuthing that went into piecing together information about him.

programme.title: Turnaround A Story Of Recovery
programme.desc: Turnaround: A Story of Recovery" follows five women battling addiction at Aurora House. This documentary offers insight for families, friends, and professionals interested in alternative treatment methods.

programme.title: The Stratford Adventure
programme.desc: How a small Canadian city, bearing the name of Stratford and by a river Avon, realized the vision of one of its sons: the creation of a theatre for the staging of the finest Shakespearean drama.

programme.title: The Thundermans: Winter Thunderland
programme.desc: Max zeigt seine garstigste Seite als Heilig Abend naht und bekommt Besuch von den Geistern der vergangenen, gegenwärtigen und zukünftigen Weihnacht. Diese bringen ihn in Festtagsstimmung.

programme.title: Dora: Fröhliche Weihnachten!
programme.desc: Dora und Boots wollen dem Weihnachtsmann ihrerseits ein Geschenk überreichen. Da sie den Augenblick verpassen, als er die Geschenke für sie abliefert, fahren sie kurz entschlossen mit ihrem Freund Blue Train Richtung Nordpol.

programme.title: Rocko's Modernes Leben: Fröhliche Weihnachten
programme.desc: Fröhliche Weihnachten: Es weihnachtet sehr - natürlich auch in O-Town. Rocko ist ganz besonders feierlich zumute, weshalb er eine große Party plant.

programme.title: The Loud House: Weihnachten bei den Louds
programme.desc: Die Weihnachtsferien haben begonnen und die Louds freuen sich auf ein schönes Fest. Doch leider landet beim Rodeln Lincolns Schlitten im Garten des griesgrämigen Nachbarn Mr. Grouse. Kann sich Lincoln seinen geliebten Schlitten zurückholen?

programme.title: The Fairly Odd Parents: Fröhliche Wunschnachten!
programme.desc: Timmy bekommt nicht das zu Weihnachten, was er möchte. Also wünscht er es sich einfach. Seine Freunde können das nicht, darum wünscht sich Timmy für alle Kinder einen Zaubergutschein, mit dem sie sich einen Wunsch erfüllen können.

programme.title: Danny Phantom: Der Weihnachtsspuk
programme.desc: Danny hasst Weihnachten. Als Danny versehentlich die einzige Kopie einer Weihnachtsgeistergeschichte zerstört, verwandelt ihn der Autor des Buches in die Hauptfigur einer neuen Weihnachtsgeschichte.

programme.title: Nickelodeon's Ho Ho Holiday Special: Nickelodeon's Ho Ho Holiday Special
programme.desc: Deine Nickelodeon Stars treffen sich zur besten Weihnachtsparty aller Zeiten. Es geht los mit cooler Musik und lustigen Sketchen, doch bald merken unsere Helden, dass ihnen eine Falle gestellt wurde!

programme.title: Rugrats: Im Spielzeugland, Teil 2
programme.desc: Die Babys besuchen mit ihren Eltern das Feriendorf von Stu. Während sich die Erwachsenen in der Western-Holzhütte einsperren, versucht Angelika Santa Clause seinen Job aufzugeben. Können die Rugrats das angerichtete Chaos wieder in Ordnung bringen?

programme.title: Bubble Guppies: Eine fröhliche Guppy-Weihnacht
programme.desc: Auf der Weihnachtsbaumfarm lernen die Guppies Herrn Klaus und sein Pferd Schneeflocke kennen. Ob Herr Klaus der Weihnachtsmann ist?

programme.title: Get Blake!: Schnappt euch den Schlafsack! / Schnappt euch die Stiefel!
programme.desc: Die Space-Hörnchen sprühen Roy mit Einschlafspray ein und verschaffen ihm so das verrückteste Date aller Zeiten. // Blake will seine Schuhe kaputtmachen, damit sein Vater ihm Unzerstör-Boots kauft.
programme.sub-title: Schnappt euch den Schlafsack! / Schnappt euch die Stiefel!

programme.title: Bucket & Skinner's Epic Adventures: Superweihnachten
programme.desc: Buckets jährlicher Familienausflug zu Weihnachten ist ins Wasser gefallen. Das drückt die Stimmung gewaltig. Doch als Bucket einschläft, trifft ihn eine Überraschung...

programme.title: Regal Academy: Die Falle der Schneekönigin
programme.desc: Um gegen die sechs großen Märchenfamilien anzukommen, lässt die Schneekönigin Hawks Schwester Fala frei, die sie vor Jahren entführt hat, und benutzt sie als Spielfigur innerhalb der Schule.

programme.title: Game Shakers: Weihnachten mit Reggae Potato
programme.desc: Double G tritt als Reggae Potato mit einem Weihnachts-Special live im Fernsehen auf, aber als die Sendung losgeht, fangen seine Haare Feuer und die Game Shakers müssen für ihn einspringen.

programme.title: iCarly: Ein Schrottbaum zu Weihnachten
programme.desc: Um Weihnachten etwas aufzupeppen baut Spencer einen unkonventionellen Weihnachtsbaum, der versehentlich Feuer fängt und alle Geschenke verbrennt. Craly ist enttäuscht und wünscht sich einen normalen Bruder.

programme.title: Hey Arnold: Hitzewelle / Der erste Schnee
programme.desc: Die Stadt wird von einer Hitzewelle erfasst und ein Eisverkäufer, der seine Erfrischungen zu Wucherpreisen an den Mann bringt./Der erste Schnee ist gefallen. Arnold kann es kaum erwarten, hinaus zu gehen und mit seinen Freunden Schlitten zu fahren.

programme.title: The Adventures of Jimmy Neutron: Das fast ausgefallene Weihnachtsfest
programme.desc: Jimmy ist fest davon überzeugt, dass es den Weihnachtsmann nicht gibt.Um seine Theorie zu untermauern,reist er mit Carl und Max an den Nordpol.Dort entdecken sie eine Spielzeugfabrik - und plötzlich taucht eine große Gestalt auf - der Weihnachtsmann

programme.title: SpongeBob Schwammkopf: Weihnachten unter Wasser
programme.desc: Sandy erzählt SpongeBob von Weihnachten und vom Weihnachtsmann. Sponge ist natürlich hellauf begeistert und erzählt in der ganzen Stadt davon. Nun schreiben alle brav ihre Wunschzettel und warten aufs Christkind, nein, den Weihnachtsmann.

programme.title: Wonder Pets: Rettet das Rentier!
programme.desc: Linny, Ming-Ming, und Tuck starten zu einer vorweihnachtlichen Rettungsmission: Sie müssen eins der Rentiere des Weihnachtsmanns befreien, das im ewigen Eis am Nordpol feststeckt.

programme.desc: Ein MTV Unplugged-Konzert ist die Königsdisziplin für jeden Künstler. Im August 2017 nahm nun Peter Maffay sein MTV Unplugged auf. Auf der Bühne unterstützen ihn dabei u.a. Johannes Oerding, Katie Melua, Jennifer Weist & Philipp Poisel.

programme.desc: Ännu en klassisk MTV Unplugged Mando Diao - en avskalad konsert från bandets skiva ”Efter Solnedgången”.

programme.desc: Das erste MTV Unplugged auf hoher See! Samy Deluxe setzt mit Max Herre, den Beginnern, Nena und vielen anderen die Segel auf der MS Bleichen in Hamburg für das SaMTV Unplugged.

programme.title: MTV Unplugged: a-ha
programme.desc: Im Juni 2017 zeichneten a-ha, das norwegische Trio mit Millionen verkaufter Platten, ein Konzert für die legendäre Reihe "MTV Unplugged" auf. Das Event fand in der Mittsommernacht auf der kleinen norwegischen Insel Giske statt.

programme.title: Duas Vezes Suzie
programme.desc: Uma editora que acabou de se divorciar perde o interesse pela vida, mas uma menina de sete anos a faz perceber que se esqueceu de coisas importantes, como a família e um novo amor - tudo às vésperas do Natal.

programme.title: Tempo de Natal
programme.desc: Dois irmãos distantes tentam se reconectar no Natal, mas há algo que um deles não consegue superar: o outro pensa que é um viajante do tempo.

programme.title: Véspera de Natal
programme.desc: É véspera de Natal e um apagão vai obrigar alguns nova-iorquinos ocupados a ficarem presos dentro de elevadores enquanto esperam por ajuda. Essa longa noite juntos irá mudar suas vidas para sempre.

programme.title: Lucia e o Cristal Mágico
programme.desc: Lucia é a primeira menina da Escola Internacional de Natal. Quando seu melhor amigo, Oscar, é acusado de roubar o cristal mágico do Rei Inverno, que alimenta a máquina atual, Lucia se propõe a provar a inocência dele.

programme.title: O Verdadeiro Sentido do Amor
programme.desc: Na noite de Natal, o xerife Rick parece ter perdido seu espírito natalino. Quando prende um homem acusado de invadir as casas da vizinhança, o xerife não sabe o que fazer quando o invasor declara ser o Papai Noel em pessoa.

programme.title: O milagre de natal Jonathan Toomey
programme.desc: Quando um menino perde o presépio de madeira que o liga ao pai morto, sua mãe preocupada convence um entalhador solitário e mal-humorado a criar um substituto e permitir que seu filho o veja trabalhar nele.

programme.title: Casamento De Natal
programme.desc: Maggie é uma editora literária cujo hobby é criar oportunidades de relacionamento entre seus amigos. Quando seu ex-namorado aparece como um autor recém-contratado e bem-sucedido, Maggie precisa examinar suas decisões anteriores.

programme.title: Bebê a Bordo no Natal
programme.desc: Na sequência de “Um Ano Depois Daquele Natal”, nem todo mundo parece estar animado para o Natal da Família Chandler.

programme.title: Meu Pai é Ranzinza
programme.desc: Os animais da Fazenda Woodsley ajudam Oliver e sua irmã mais nova a chocar seu pai para abraçar o espírito natalino enquanto tentam salvar a fazenda.

programme.title: Um Natal Encantado
programme.desc: Hugo, de doze anos, ainda acredita em elfos, mas é provocado por seus colegas, então decide se forçar a crescer. Mas quando sua família sai de férias de Natal, ele descobre que elfos moram no hotel.

programme.title: Fabric of Christmas, The
programme.desc: Liam, un bombero, y Amy, una profesora de acolchado, se unen para hacer una colcha navideña para la boda de la hermana de Liam, pero su romance se ve amenazado por el plan de Liam de viajar a Sudamérica.

programme.title: The Santa Squad
programme.desc: Allie, una profesora de arte desempleada, acepta un trabajo para ayudar a un viudo rico y a sus dos hijas. Mientras Allie levanta el espíritu navideño de la familia con adornos navideños, su amabilidad se ve recompensada con un regalo inesperado: ¡Amor!

programme.title: The Christmas Candle
programme.desc: Un pastor que ha sufrido una pérdida personal acepta un puesto en un pueblo que cree en una vela milagrosa de Navidad, la cual se esfuerza por abolir.

programme.title: So this is Christmas
programme.desc: A los 18 años, Ashley sale con gente mala, y busca una fuga de la rutina de casa. Pero todo empieza a cambiar cuando uno de los empleados de la familia consigue animarla a hacer una pieza de teatro de Navidad para niños necesitados.

programme.title: El árbol de navidad
programme.desc: Cuando una chica de la gran ciudad (Lacey Chabert) regresa para salvar la granja de árboles de Navidad de su infancia, puede redescubrir más de lo que esperaba, incluido su único amor verdadero.

programme.title: Santa, qué?
programme.desc: En esta conmovedora historia de Navidad, donde el auténtico Papá Noel (Leslie Nielsen) se cae de su trineo y desarrolla amnesia. Luego se encuentra con un cansado periodista de televisión, quien es su única esperanza para recuperar a tiempo su memoria y p

programme.title: Una Navidad Encantada
programme.desc: Hugo, de doce años, sigue creyendo en los elfos, pero sus compañeros de clase se burlan de él y decide madurar. Pero cuando su familia se va de vacaciones de Navidad, descubre que los elfos viven en el hotel. Hugo puede lanzarse a la aventura.

programme.title: Una navidad para recordar
programme.desc: Sebastián, quien odia la Navidad y enfrenta su primer año sin sus hijos después de un divorcio, decide pasar la temporada con su madre Ángela, quien padece de Alzheimer.

programme.title: Homemade Christmas
programme.desc: Cada año, una joven quiere convertirse en la mejor asistente para contratar en Navidad. Pero cuando llega la oportunidad de salvar una fiesta de Navidad y deslumbrar a la persona que le gusta, deberá elegir entre sus aspiraciones y el hombre perfecto.

programme.title: Un Negocio Brillante
programme.desc: Dos canadienses franceses viajan a Nueva York con la idea de hacerse ricos vendiendo árboles de Navidad. La situación entre ellos es bastante tensa.

programme.title: Fabric of Christmas, The
programme.desc: Liam, un bombero, y Amy, una profesora de acolchado, se unen para hacer una colcha navideña para la boda de la hermana de Liam, pero su romance se ve amenazado por el plan de Liam de viajar a Sudamérica.

programme.title: The Santa Squad
programme.desc: Allie, una profesora de arte desempleada, acepta un trabajo para ayudar a un viudo rico y a sus dos hijas. Mientras Allie levanta el espíritu navideño de la familia con adornos navideños, su amabilidad se ve recompensada con un regalo inesperado: ¡Amor!

programme.title: The Christmas Candle
programme.desc: Un pastor que ha sufrido una pérdida personal acepta un puesto en un pueblo que cree en una vela milagrosa de Navidad, la cual se esfuerza por abolir.

programme.title: So this is Christmas
programme.desc: A los 18 años, Ashley sale con gente mala, y busca una fuga de la rutina de casa. Pero todo empieza a cambiar cuando uno de los empleados de la familia consigue animarla a hacer una pieza de teatro de Navidad para niños necesitados.

programme.title: El árbol de navidad
programme.desc: Cuando una chica de la gran ciudad (Lacey Chabert) regresa para salvar la granja de árboles de Navidad de su infancia, puede redescubrir más de lo que esperaba, incluido su único amor verdadero.

programme.title: Santa, qué?
programme.desc: En esta conmovedora historia de Navidad, donde el auténtico Papá Noel (Leslie Nielsen) se cae de su trineo y desarrolla amnesia. Luego se encuentra con un cansado periodista de televisión, quien es su única esperanza para recuperar a tiempo su memoria y p

programme.title: Una Navidad Encantada
programme.desc: Hugo, de doce años, sigue creyendo en los elfos, pero sus compañeros de clase se burlan de él y decide madurar. Pero cuando su familia se va de vacaciones de Navidad, descubre que los elfos viven en el hotel. Hugo puede lanzarse a la aventura.

programme.title: Una navidad para recordar
programme.desc: Sebastián, quien odia la Navidad y enfrenta su primer año sin sus hijos después de un divorcio, decide pasar la temporada con su madre Ángela, quien padece de Alzheimer.

programme.title: Homemade Christmas
programme.desc: Cada año, una joven quiere convertirse en la mejor asistente para contratar en Navidad. Pero cuando llega la oportunidad de salvar una fiesta de Navidad y deslumbrar a la persona que le gusta, deberá elegir entre sus aspiraciones y el hombre perfecto.

programme.title: Un Negocio Brillante
programme.desc: Dos canadienses franceses viajan a Nueva York con la idea de hacerse ricos vendiendo árboles de Navidad. La situación entre ellos es bastante tensa.

programme.title: Fabric of Christmas, The
programme.desc: Liam, un bombero, y Amy, una profesora de acolchado, se unen para hacer una colcha navideña para la boda de la hermana de Liam, pero su romance se ve amenazado por el plan de Liam de viajar a Sudamérica.

programme.title: The Santa Squad
programme.desc: Allie, una profesora de arte desempleada, acepta un trabajo para ayudar a un viudo rico y a sus dos hijas. Mientras Allie levanta el espíritu navideño de la familia con adornos navideños, su amabilidad se ve recompensada con un regalo inesperado: ¡Amor!

programme.title: The Christmas Candle
programme.desc: Un pastor que ha sufrido una pérdida personal acepta un puesto en un pueblo que cree en una vela milagrosa de Navidad, la cual se esfuerza por abolir.

programme.title: So this is Christmas
programme.desc: A los 18 años, Ashley sale con gente mala, y busca una fuga de la rutina de casa. Pero todo empieza a cambiar cuando uno de los empleados de la familia consigue animarla a hacer una pieza de teatro de Navidad para niños necesitados.

programme.title: El árbol de navidad
programme.desc: Cuando una chica de la gran ciudad (Lacey Chabert) regresa para salvar la granja de árboles de Navidad de su infancia, puede redescubrir más de lo que esperaba, incluido su único amor verdadero.

programme.title: Santa, qué?
programme.desc: En esta conmovedora historia de Navidad, donde el auténtico Papá Noel (Leslie Nielsen) se cae de su trineo y desarrolla amnesia. Luego se encuentra con un cansado periodista de televisión, quien es su única esperanza para recuperar a tiempo su memoria y p

programme.title: Una Navidad Encantada
programme.desc: Hugo, de doce años, sigue creyendo en los elfos, pero sus compañeros de clase se burlan de él y decide madurar. Pero cuando su familia se va de vacaciones de Navidad, descubre que los elfos viven en el hotel. Hugo puede lanzarse a la aventura.

programme.title: Una navidad para recordar
programme.desc: Sebastián, quien odia la Navidad y enfrenta su primer año sin sus hijos después de un divorcio, decide pasar la temporada con su madre Ángela, quien padece de Alzheimer.

programme.title: Homemade Christmas
programme.desc: Cada año, una joven quiere convertirse en la mejor asistente para contratar en Navidad. Pero cuando llega la oportunidad de salvar una fiesta de Navidad y deslumbrar a la persona que le gusta, deberá elegir entre sus aspiraciones y el hombre perfecto.

programme.title: Un Negocio Brillante
programme.desc: Dos canadienses franceses viajan a Nueva York con la idea de hacerse ricos vendiendo árboles de Navidad. La situación entre ellos es bastante tensa.

programme.title: DIE HALBINSEL
programme.desc: Die Küste der Iberischen Halbinsel trifft sowohl auf den Atlantischen Ozean als auch auf das Mittelmeer. Es ist einer der reichsten ozeanischen Lebensräume Europas. Es beherbergt Tausende von Wildtierarten. Entlang der 3000 km² großen Küste finden wir schroffe Klippen, Dünensysteme und ausgedehnte Sandstrände, Flussmündungen und Marschland. Alle diese Landschaften sind ein geologisches Zeugnis der Vergangenheit der Halbinsel und jede von ihnen beherbergt unterschiedliche Lebensformen, die zum Gleichgewicht der natürlichen Welt beitragen.

programme.title: Mitten im Südafrika
programme.desc: Wieder einmal verwandelt sich das Land. Andreas und das Teams lernen eine ganz neue Seite Südafrikas kennen. Inzwischen haben sie schon mehr als 2000 Kilometer Strecke hinter sich gebracht.

programme.title: Mitten im Südafrika
programme.desc: Das Meer verwandelt sich zusehends. Die azurblaue See von Durban unterscheidet sich grundlegend von der rauen Meeresküste des Kaps. Gemeinsam mit dem österreichischen Haiforscher Dietmar Posch startet Andreas auf eine Expedition in die warmen Gewässer vor der Küste

programme.title: Mitten im Südafrika
programme.desc: Andreas lange Reise führt ihn schließlich und endlich in den Busch – ins „echte“ Afrika. Hier begibt er sich auf die Fährte der typischsten wilden Afrikaner – der Big Five. Und wo könnte er das besser als im Krüger Nationalpark, dem Wahrzeichen Südafrikas.

programme.title: DIE HALBINSEL
programme.desc: Einer der symbolträchtigsten Lebensräume der iberischen Halbinsel ist der Mittelmeerwald, das Land des Iberischen Luchses, einer einzigartigen und faszinierenden Raubkatze mit einer Erfolgsgeschichte bei der Erhaltung der Tiere. Korkeichen und Steineichen sind die Herren dieser herrlichen Wälder. Und diese Wälder beherbergen eine einzigartige und endemische Fauna. Damit ist diese Region einer der wichtigsten Biodiversitäts-Hotspots der Erde.

programme.title: DIE HALBINSEL
programme.desc: Berge sind für die gesamte Morphologie Iberiens verantwortlich. Sie sind auch der Geburtsort der Flüsse, die das Leben im gesamten Gebiet verteilen. Hier gibt es viele Wälder, jeder mit seinem eigenen Ökosystem. Iberische Gebirgsketten haben unterschiedliche Gesichter und Persönlichkeiten, ebenso wie ihre wilden Bewohner.

Doch die meisten sind schwach und mangelernährt. Parasiten und Seuchen setzen den Wiederkäuern zu. Innovative Futterblöcke könnten die Situation verbessern.

programme.title: Paris, Blitz Motorcycles
programme.desc: Fred Jourden und Hugo Jezegabel haben ihre Leidenschaft zum Beruf und zum Geschäft gemacht: In ihrer Werkstatt mitten in Paris fertigen sie kunstvoll aus alten Motorrädern neue, ganz besondere Zweiräder. Jedes Exemplar ist ein Unikat.

programme.title: Kambodscha
programme.desc: Der Japaner Kikuo Morimoto fördert in Kambodscha die traditionelle Webkunst und verschafft mit der Anpflanzung von Maulbeerbäumen und der Herstellung hochwertiger Seidenstoffe Hunderten von Menschen ein Einkommen. Er geht wie jeden Morgen durch die Reihen der 300 Frauen, die in seiner Seiden-Weberei arbeiten. Der ehemalige Kimonomaler war vor 15 Jahren, bei seiner ersten Reise nach Phnom Penh, auf die Spur der fast ausgelöschten Tradition der Seidenweberei gestoßen. Ausgelöscht während der Diktatur der Roten Khmer und dem nachfolgenden Bürgerkrieg, unter dem Kambodscha jahrzehntelang gelitten hat. Für ihr Ziel, den neuen Menschen zu schaffen, zertrümmerten die Roten Khmer im Namen eines Steinzeit-Kommunismus alles Geistige und Sinnliche im Lande. Damit verschwand beinahe auch die einmalige Kunst der Seidenherstellung. Morimoto grub die alten Rezepturen des Färbens wieder aus: rot aus dem Saft der Lackschildläuse, braun vom Sud der Kokosnussschalen, grau durch die ausgekochten Äste des Lychee-Baums. Und er studierte die in Vergessenheit geratenen, über 1200 Jahre alten Muster. 1996 gründete er schließlich eine Weberei. Im ganzen Land konnte er nur noch ein Dutzend Weberinnen aufspüren und für sein Projekt begeistern. Sie verließen ihre Dörfer und zogen mit ihm nach Siem Reap, ...

programme.title: Die Verwandlungskünstler von Dakar
programme.desc: Dakar, die Hauptstadt Senegals: Hier zu überleben, ist für viele Menschen eine Frage der Improvisation. In vielen Vierteln hat die Not einen ganz eigenen Boom hervorgebracht: Die Menschen sammeln, was andere weggeworfen haben - und wandeln diese Abfälle in Neues? um. Wir zeigen, wie alte Konservendosen in Spielzeugautos, Lampen und Koffer verwandelt werden, Kronkorken in Körbe, Motoren in Kochtöpfe, Autoreifen in Eimer. So entstehen Gebrauchsgegenstände, aber auch Spielzeuge und Möbelstücke, die in Europa bereits als Kleinkunst gehandelt werden. Der 31-Jährige Malick Mbaye weiß zu schätzen, was andere Menschen wegwerfen: Büchsen, Dosen und Flaschendeckel - oder alte Paletten. Zusammen mit seinem Kompagnon Alassane Diop, 26, bastelt er daraus mit meist improvisierten Werkzeugen Kommoden, Koffer oder Gießkannen, aber auch Spielzeug. Sogar aus Europa erhalten die beiden inzwischen Aufträge. Mit ihrer kleinen Werkstatt Soweto Village? können sie ihre Eltern und Geschwister ernähren, für eigene Familien allerdings reicht das bescheidene Einkommen nicht. Lebenstraum der beiden ist es, eines Tages alle Freunde und Verwandte beschäftigen zu können.Schon jetzt ist ihre Veranda sozialer Mittelpunkt der Nachbarschaft. Ganze Stadtteile Dakars leben von der Müll-Verwandlung. Aus Mangel an ...

programme.title: Die Marmorberge von Italien
programme.desc: Die Apuanischen Alpen im Nordwesten der Toskana beherbergen eines der größten Marmorvorkommen der Welt. Seit der Römerzeit wird hier der weltberühmte Carrara-Marmor abgebaut. Mit allen Mitteln der Technik ringt der Mensch dem Berg das wertvolle Gestein ab und transportiert es auf halsbrecherischen Wegen ins Tal, von wo aus seine Reise in die ganze Welt beginnt. Am frühen Morgen fährt der Bildhauer Renzo Maggi zum 1.300 Meter hoch gelegenen Marmorbruch von Monte Cervaiole. Bereits Michelangelo hat sich hier im 16. Jahrhundert seine gigantischen Marmorblöcke ausgesucht. Trotz moderner Technik wird die Marmorgewinnung größtenteils noch auf traditionelle Weise betrieben. Teilweise unter lebensgefährlichen Bedingungen: Extreme Wetterschwankungen und Nebel erschweren den Einsatz von schwerem Gerät. Auf halsbrecherischen Serpentinen wird die tonnenschwere Last dann hinab zum Hafen von Carrara gebracht, von wo aus der Marmor seine Reise in die ganze Welt antritt.

programme.title: Die letzten Cowboys der Toskana
programme.desc: Im Herzen der Maremma, der Küstenregion der Toskana, werden auf einer Azienda seit mehr als 1000 Jahren Rinder und Pferde gezüchtet. Butteri, wie hier die Rinderhirten genannt werden, sind wind- und wetterfeste Kerle. Am ersten Mai steht die Merca? an, das ist der wichtigste Tag des Jahres für jeden Buttero. Dann werden die wildlebenden Kälber von den Müttern getrennt und wie anno dazumal mit Brandeisen markiert.

programme.title: Burundi
programme.desc: Désiré Nininahazwe, Familienvater und Gründer eines Start ups, kam zum ersten Mal mit dem Trommeln in Kontakt, als er ins SOS-Kinderdorf nach Bujumbura kam, nachdem er seine Eltern im Bürgerkrieg verloren hatte.

programme.title: Madagaskar
programme.sub-title: Die junge Generation im Spannungsfeld des Klimawandels
programme.desc: Während man im westlichen Ausland an Vanilleplantagen und Tropenwälder denkt, spricht man in Madagaskar nur noch von Kéré, der schlimmsten Dürre seit 40 Jahren. Hoffnung gibt, dass sich die SOS-Kinderdörfer um die Kinder des Dorfes kümmern.

programme.title: Sri Lanka

programme.title: Astrud Gilberto & Dizzy Gillespie
programme.sub-title: Gilberto, Gillespie & Skymasters - North Sea Jazz
programme.desc: The North Sea Jazz Festival is the largest indoor music festival in the world, known globally as the event where the past, present and future of jazz are featured within three days. Next to a firm base of jazz as the festival's staple music genre, many others, such as blues, soul, funk, or hip hop, pass by. In 1982, Dutch big band The Skymasters accompanied monumental jazz trumpet legend Dizzy Gillespie and the Brazilian bossa nova singer Astrud Gilberto at the North Sea Jazz Festival in The Hague.

programme.title: George Shearing & Neil Swanson
programme.sub-title: George Shearing Duo feat. Neil Swainson
programme.desc: British pianist George Shearing enjoyed an international reputation as an instrumentalist, arranger, and composer. Equally at home on the classical concert stage as in jazz clubs, he was recognized for his inventive, orchestrated jazz. In this live recording from the Munich Philharmonie, Shearing played in a duo format with Canadian double bassist Neil Swainson. The repertoire consisted of a selection of compositions by Shearing himself, among them ‘Lullaby Of Birdland', which is a standard in jazz repertoire.

programme.title: Trombone Shorty
programme.sub-title: Troy 'Trombone Shorty' Andrews: Jazz à Vienne
programme.desc: Jazz phenomenon Trombone Shorty dishes out a mix of funk, jazz, hip-hop and soul at this concert at the French festival Jazz à Vienne. Playing with the energy of a rock star, Troy Andrews, a.k.a. ‘Trombone Shorty', pays homage to jazz legends. With his hypnotic performance and boundless energy, Trombone Shorty puts up an unparalleled performance.

programme.title: Jon Hendricks, Judith Hendricks, Kim Lindsay & Mart Ledford
programme.desc: Since 1977, Estival is a summer jazz festival in Switzerland, Lugano. Estival offers a thrilling and particularly surprising line-up that explores the rich world of contemporary music whilst promoting the understanding of different cultures, tolerance, and co-existence. John Carl Hendricks is one of the instigators of "vocalese", an art form that aims to add lyrics to existing instrumental pieces and replace several instruments with singing. He flaunts this technique at Estival, where he "scat" while playing double bass. Hendricks is known for his mastery of scat, a form of vocal jazz that uses onomatopoeia rather than lyrics

programme.title: Philip Catherine, Jean-Louis Rassinfosse & Chet Baker
programme.sub-title: Jazz a la Grand Place Chet Baker Trio
programme.desc: Two top-tier Belgian musicians – guitarist Philip Catherine and bassist Jean-Louis Rassinfosse – accompany American jazz trumpeter and vocalist Chet Baker during this 1985 performance at the beautiful Brussels Jazz Club, located on the Grand-Place, the Belgian capital's central square. The trio plays Charlie Mariano's “Crystal Bells”, the title track of their acclaimed 1983 album. Other songs played during this legendary concert include “Down” and “How Deep is the Ocean”.

Abbey Road Studios remains an icon of music and recording, you know, there must be something in the walls of the place, the amount of incredible pieces of music, which have been recorded in that building, it's a tourist attraction people want to be near it they want to say they've been to Abbey Road, because it's so important

programme.title: Sun Record Years
programme.desc: Sun Records, as a label, was one of the founding fathers of Rock and Roll. Sam Phillips had the vision of what Rock and Roll could, would, and might become. And no-one else had that. These weren't songs that were incredibly difficult to play. They were exciting, short, basic, fun, tended to have a simple message, the reason it became so successful, is because people could emulate it. Sun Records really laid the foundation of what was Rock and Roll music. Those artists really created something new, and something that has endured and influenced so many bands throughout the years

programme.title: Adrien Perruchon, Symfonieorkest Vlaanderen & Josef Špaček
programme.sub-title: Works by Ravel, Lalo, Ginastera a. o.
programme.desc: French conductor Adrien Perruchon and the Flanders Symphony Orchestra take us on a musical journey to Argentine, Spain, and Mexico, in this March 1, 2017 concert performance at Concertgebouw Brugge in Belgium. The program opens with Édouard Lalo's Spanish Symphony for violin and orchestra, Op. 21, featuring Czech violinist Josef Špaček as the soloist. This is followed by Mathias Coppens' Music for Orchestra, Op. 12. The program continues with Alberto Ginastera's Dances from Estancia, Op. 8a, and Aaron Copland's El Salón México. Also on the program is Maurice Ravel's famous Boléro. The program comes to a close with Arturo Márquez's Danzón No. 2.

programme.title: Evgeny Kissin, Nikolai Demidenko, Warsaw Philharmonic Orchestra & Antoni Wit
programme.desc: Antoni Wit conducts the Warsaw Philharmonic Orchestra in performances of Chopin's Piano Concertos No. 1, Op. 11 and No. 2, Op. 21. Soloists are Nikolai Demidenko and Evgeny Kissin. After performing the first concerto, Demidenko encores with Chopin's Mazurka Op. 17/4. Kissin closes the concert with Chopin's Etude Op. 10/12 and the Waltz in E minor, Op. post. This concert was part of the celebration of Chopin's 200th anniversary in 2010. Chopin composed the second concerto one year before the Concerto No. 1 and completed both works at the age of 20, before leaving his home country Poland and moving to Paris.

programme.title: Herbert Blomstedt & Gewandhausorchester Leipzig
programme.sub-title: Symphonies in D by Mozart and Voríšek
programme.desc: Conductor Herbert Blomstedt and the Gewandhausorchester take us on a musical journey to the Czech Republic in this 2020 concert from Leipzig's Gewandhaus. The program opens with Bohemian composer Jan Václav Hugo Voríšek's Symphony in D major, Op. 23 (1821). Although the composition – Voríšek's only symphony – was never performed during the composer's lifetime, it has become one of his most-performed works today. Also on the program is Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart's Symphony No. 38 in D major, K. 504. This work, which premiered while Mozart was visiting Prague in 1787, is often referred to as the ‘Prague Symphony'.

programme.title: Ivan Fischer, Budapest Festival Orchestra & Richard Goode
programme.sub-title: Beethoven - Symphonies and Piano Concerto No. 4
programme.desc: Iván Fischer leads his Budapest Festival Orchestra (BFO) in a concert program dedicated to the music of Ludwig van Beethoven. The program opens with the composer's Symphony No. 1 in C major, Op. 21. Afterward, Fischer conducts Beethoven's Piano Concerto No. 4 in G major, Op. 58, in which Richard Goode features as the soloist. The acclaimed American pianist (1943) is known for his interpretations of the Beethoven repertoire. Goode recorded all five Beethoven piano concertos with the BFO and Fischer, earning him exceptional critical acclaim and a Grammy Award nomination. As an encore, Goode performs the Sarabande from J. S. Bach's Partita in B-flat major, BWV 825. The program closes with Beethoven's famous Symphony No. 5 in C minor, Op. 67. This performance was recorded at the Béla Bartók National Concert Hall in Budapest, Hungary, on January 29, 2017.

programme.title: Flying Over Iceland II
programme.desc: Experience the wonders of summertime in Iceland from an elevated perspective with "Flying Over Iceland II: Summer in the Golden Circle". Filmed during quarantine in September of 2020, ambient film features an immersive slow-moving aerial perspective of some of Islandia's most iconic and famous south coast loop locations - all in glorious sunlight. Beginning at the stunning 200 foot high Skogafoss waterfall, viewers next are gently flown to the charming coastal city of Vik, which overlooks the famous Vikurfjara Black Sand Beach. Here ancient lava flows have sculpted some impressive coastal outcroppings which viewers will witness from a bird's eye view, before soaring to great heights in order to witness the distant glaciers and unique geography of South Iceland as never seen before. From the black sand beach we then soar west to the charming Dyrholaey Lighthouse, which also sits atop some absolutely stunning coastal rock formations including a giant arch at sea level. After returning to Vik the film next progresses to the glacier Vatnajökull, offering majestic views of Iceland's largest glacier. From soaring above the misty clouds to dipping down into the ice formations, the film ends with multiple unique perspectives of the glacial area including young pine forests, a visit from some local sheep, and a journey above and below the clouds for one final refreshing cap to the 1 hour film.

programme.title: DIE HALBINSEL
programme.desc: Die Küste der Iberischen Halbinsel trifft sowohl auf den Atlantischen Ozean als auch auf das Mittelmeer. Es ist einer der reichsten ozeanischen Lebensräume Europas. Es beherbergt Tausende von Wildtierarten. Entlang der 3000 km² großen Küste finden wir schroffe Klippen, Dünensysteme und ausgedehnte Sandstrände, Flussmündungen und Marschland. Alle diese Landschaften sind ein geologisches Zeugnis der Vergangenheit der Halbinsel und jede von ihnen beherbergt unterschiedliche Lebensformen, die zum Gleichgewicht der natürlichen Welt beitragen.

programme.title: Mitten im Südafrika

programme.title: DIE HALBINSEL

Korkeichen und Steineichen sind die Herren dieser herrlichen Wälder. Und diese Wälder beherbergen eine einzigartige und endemische Fauna. Damit ist diese Region einer der wichtigsten Biodiversitäts-Hotspots der Erde.

programme.title: Laos
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Wasserbüffel gelten in Laos als "Sparbücher für Notzeiten". Muss jemand ins Krankenhaus, geht der Reis aus oder steht eine Hochzeit an, verkauft man einen Büffel. Doch die meisten sind schwach und mangelernährt. Parasiten und Seuchen setzen den Wiederkäuern zu. Innovative Futterblöcke könnten die Situation verbessern.

programme.title: Just Cooking | Trailer
programme.desc: Just Cooking bringt Kochbegeisterten das einzigartige Paket an frischen neuen Food-Trends und junger Kreativität auf den TV. Aber auch Klassiker und traditionelle Küche, sowie kulinarische Dokumentationen und Reisevlogs werden gezeigt.

programme.title: Paris, Blitz Motorcycles
programme.desc: Fred Jourden und Hugo Jezegabel haben ihre Leidenschaft zum Beruf und zum Geschäft gemacht: In ihrer Werkstatt mitten in Paris fertigen sie kunstvoll aus alten Motorrädern neue, ganz besondere Zweiräder. Jedes Exemplar ist ein Unikat.

programme.title: Kambodscha
programme.desc: Der Japaner Kikuo Morimoto fördert in Kambodscha die traditionelle Webkunst und verschafft mit der Anpflanzung von Maulbeerbäumen und der Herstellung hochwertiger Seidenstoffe Hunderten von Menschen ein Einkommen. Er geht wie jeden Morgen durch die Reihen der 300 Frauen, die in seiner Seiden-Weberei arbeiten. Der ehemalige Kimonomaler war vor 15 Jahren, bei seiner ersten Reise nach Phnom Penh, auf die Spur der fast ausgelöschten Tradition der Seidenweberei gestoßen. Ausgelöscht während der Diktatur der Roten Khmer und dem nachfolgenden Bürgerkrieg, unter dem Kambodscha jahrzehntelang gelitten hat. Für ihr Ziel, den neuen Menschen zu schaffen, zertrümmerten die Roten Khmer im Namen eines Steinzeit-Kommunismus alles Geistige und Sinnliche im Lande. Damit verschwand beinahe auch die einmalige Kunst der Seidenherstellung. Morimoto grub die alten Rezepturen des Färbens wieder aus: rot aus dem Saft der Lackschildläuse, braun vom Sud der Kokosnussschalen, grau durch die ausgekochten Äste des Lychee-Baums. Und er studierte die in Vergessenheit geratenen, über 1200 Jahre alten Muster. 1996 gründete er schließlich eine Weberei. Im ganzen Land konnte er nur noch ein Dutzend Weberinnen aufspüren und für sein Projekt begeistern. Sie verließen ihre Dörfer und zogen mit ihm nach Siem Reap, ...

programme.title: Die Verwandlungskünstler von Dakar
programme.desc: Dakar, die Hauptstadt Senegals: Hier zu überleben, ist für viele Menschen eine Frage der Improvisation. In vielen Vierteln hat die Not einen ganz eigenen Boom hervorgebracht: Die Menschen sammeln, was andere weggeworfen haben - und wandeln diese Abfälle in Neues? um. Wir zeigen, wie alte Konservendosen in Spielzeugautos, Lampen und Koffer verwandelt werden, Kronkorken in Körbe, Motoren in Kochtöpfe, Autoreifen in Eimer. So entstehen Gebrauchsgegenstände, aber auch Spielzeuge und Möbelstücke, die in Europa bereits als Kleinkunst gehandelt werden. Der 31-Jährige Malick Mbaye weiß zu schätzen, was andere Menschen wegwerfen: Büchsen, Dosen und Flaschendeckel - oder alte Paletten. Zusammen mit seinem Kompagnon Alassane Diop, 26, bastelt er daraus mit meist improvisierten Werkzeugen Kommoden, Koffer oder Gießkannen, aber auch Spielzeug. Sogar aus Europa erhalten die beiden inzwischen Aufträge. Mit ihrer kleinen Werkstatt Soweto Village? können sie ihre Eltern und Geschwister ernähren, für eigene Familien allerdings reicht das bescheidene Einkommen nicht. Lebenstraum der beiden ist es, eines Tages alle Freunde und Verwandte beschäftigen zu können.Schon jetzt ist ihre Veranda sozialer Mittelpunkt der Nachbarschaft. Ganze Stadtteile Dakars leben von der Müll-Verwandlung. Aus Mangel an ...

programme.title: Die Marmorberge von Italien
programme.desc: Die Apuanischen Alpen im Nordwesten der Toskana beherbergen eines der größten Marmorvorkommen der Welt. Seit der Römerzeit wird hier der weltberühmte Carrara-Marmor abgebaut. Mit allen Mitteln der Technik ringt der Mensch dem Berg das wertvolle Gestein ab und transportiert es auf halsbrecherischen Wegen ins Tal, von wo aus seine Reise in die ganze Welt beginnt. Am frühen Morgen fährt der Bildhauer Renzo Maggi zum 1.300 Meter hoch gelegenen Marmorbruch von Monte Cervaiole. Bereits Michelangelo hat sich hier im 16. Jahrhundert seine gigantischen Marmorblöcke ausgesucht. Trotz moderner Technik wird die Marmorgewinnung größtenteils noch auf traditionelle Weise betrieben. Teilweise unter lebensgefährlichen Bedingungen: Extreme Wetterschwankungen und Nebel erschweren den Einsatz von schwerem Gerät. Auf halsbrecherischen Serpentinen wird die tonnenschwere Last dann hinab zum Hafen von Carrara gebracht, von wo aus der Marmor seine Reise in die ganze Welt antritt.

programme.title: Die letzten Cowboys der Toskana
programme.desc: Im Herzen der Maremma, der Küstenregion der Toskana, werden auf einer Azienda seit mehr als 1000 Jahren Rinder und Pferde gezüchtet. Butteri, wie hier die Rinderhirten genannt werden, sind wind- und wetterfeste Kerle. Am ersten Mai steht die Merca? an, das ist der wichtigste Tag des Jahres für jeden Buttero. Dann werden die wildlebenden Kälber von den Müttern getrennt und wie anno dazumal mit Brandeisen markiert.

programme.desc: Dopo la caduta dell'Unione Sovietica, all'inizio degli anni Novanta molti Paesi sono rimasti in conflitto, nonostante l'indipendenza dell'Europa orientale. Nel 1994 scoppiò un aspro conflitto tra le forze del movimento indipendentista ceceno e l'esercito regolare russo. Nonostante la forza lavoro, l'armamento e il supporto aereo siano stati schiaccianti, le forze russe non sono state in grado di stabilire un controllo permanente effettivo sull'area montuosa a causa dei numerosi raid della guerriglia cecena. Gli ordigni esplosivi improvvisati sono stati uno dei metodi più efficaci impiegati in queste incursioni disastrose e hanno fatto da sfondo a molti scenari di battaglia ravvicinata scambiati tra le due parti.
